  "chapter": {
    "number": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Father’s Discipline"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A wise son heeds his father’s discipline,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a mocker does not listen to rebuke.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From the fruit of his lips a man enjoys good things,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the desire of the faithless is violence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who guards his mouth protects his life,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the one who opens his lips invites his own ruin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The slacker craves yet has nothing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the soul of the diligent is fully satisfied.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The righteous hate falsehood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the wicked bring shame and disgrace.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Righteousness guards the man of integrity,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but wickedness undermines the sinner.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One pretends to be rich, but has nothing;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "another pretends to be poor, yet has great wealth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Riches may ransom a man’s life,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a poor man hears no threat.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The light of the righteous shines brightly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the lamp of the wicked is extinguished.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Arrogance leads only to strife,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but wisdom is with the well-advised.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Dishonest wealth will dwindle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but what is earned through hard work will be multiplied.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hope deferred makes the heart sick,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but desire fulfilled is a tree of life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who despises instruction will pay the penalty,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the one who respects a command will be rewarded.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The teaching",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4226
          },
          {
            "text": "of the wise is a fountain of life,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "turning one from the snares of death.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Good understanding wins favor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the way of the faithless is difficult.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Every prudent man acts with knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a fool displays his folly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A wicked messenger falls into trouble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a faithful envoy brings healing.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Poverty and shame come to him who ignores discipline,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever heeds correction is honored.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Desire fulfilled is sweet to the soul,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but turning from evil is detestable to fools.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who walks with the wise will become wise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the companion of fools will be destroyed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Disaster pursues sinners,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but prosperity is the reward of the righteous.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A good man leaves an inheritance to his children’s children,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the sinner’s wealth is passed to the righteous.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Abundant food is in the fallow ground of the poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but without justice it is swept away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who spares the rod hates his son,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who loves him disciplines him diligently.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A righteous man eats to his heart’s content,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the stomach of the wicked is empty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
